 In treatment naïve patients with newly diagnosed IIM, muscle tissue and peripheral blood share expanded BcR clones. In our study a higher cumulative frequency of dominant BcR clones in blood before treatment was associated with a higher CK and better treatment response, suggesting that response to IVIg may depend on the composition of the pre-treatment BcR repertoire.
