Humoral and cellular immunity in patients with rare autoimmune rheumatic diseases following SARS-CoV-2 vaccination.
Following two doses, most RAIRD patients have lower antibody levels than the lowest HC and lower anti-spike T cells. RAIRD patients with low/no antibodies have diminished numbers and poor quality of memory T cells which lack proliferative and functional capacities.
